%% Runtime view — CLI invocation sequence for a typical OpenAPI request.
%% (GraphQL is structurally identical; substitute the GraphQL path.)

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as Caller<br/>(human / agent / CI)
    participant M as cli/&lt;name&gt;/main.rs<br/>(CliApp::run)
    participant SP as openapi/parser<br/>+ overlay
    participant CB as openapi/commands<br/>(clap::Command builder)
    participant EI as early_intercept
    participant CL as clap parse
    participant AU as auth/compose<br/>(RoutingAuthProvider)
    participant EX as openapi/executor
    participant HC as http::HttpConfig
    participant API as Target API
    participant FP as formatter<br/>(OutputPipeline)
    participant OUT as stdout / stderr

    U->>M: $ <cli> <subcommand> [flags]
    M->>SP: parse include_str! spec (+ overlays / overrides)
    SP-->>M: RestDescription
    M->>CB: build clap::Command tree
    CB-->>M: Command (cached for this process)

    M->>EI: short-circuit?<br/>(completion / man / errors)
    alt completion or man or errors subcommand
        EI-->>OUT: emit and exit
    end

    M->>CL: parse argv against Command
    CL-->>M: ArgMatches

    M->>AU: resolve auth for matched operation
    AU->>AU: pick first security: requirement<br/>that all bound providers can satisfy
    AU-->>EX: AuthProvider handle (applied later inside request)

    M->>HC: build reqwest::Client from HttpConfig<br/>(reads &lt;NAME&gt;_CA_BUNDLE, _INSECURE, _PROXY, _TIMEOUT_SECS)
    HC-->>EX: reqwest::Client

    M->>EX: execute(operation, args)
    EX->>EX: percent-encode path segments<br/>(validate::encode_path_segment)
    EX->>AU: AuthProvider::apply(request, endpoint)
    AU-->>EX: request with auth headers
    EX->>API: HTTP request
    alt retryable status + x-fern-retries enabled + !--no-retry
        API-->>EX: retryable status
        EX->>EX: backoff with real-entropy jitter
        EX->>API: HTTP retry
    end
    API-->>EX: HTTP response
    EX->>FP: response body + format flags

    FP->>FP: --json projection / --jq / --template / colors
    FP-->>OUT: stdout (body)
    alt error
        EX-->>OUT: stdout (CliError JSON) + stderr (color label + hint)
    end
